50|$|The initial {{interest}} rate, or IIR, is {{the actual}} note rate at which interest accrues on the outstanding loan balance on an annual basis. For fixed-rate <b>reverse</b> <b>mortgages,</b> the IIR can never change. For adjustable-rate <b>reverse</b> <b>mortgages,</b> the IIR can change with program limits up to a lifetime interest rate cap.|$|R
